  "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nMaxListenersExceededWarning when running beacon node with attached validator client (does not show up if no VC is attached)\r\n\r\n```\r\n(node:67035) MaxListenersExceededWarning: Possible EventEmitter memory leak detected. 11 message listeners added to [Worker]. Use emitter.setMaxListeners() to increase limit\r\n    at _addListener (node:events:587:17)\r\n    at Worker.addListener (node:events:605:10)\r\n    at Worker.addEventListener (/home/devops/goerli/lodestar/node_modules/@chainsafe/threads/dist/master/implementation.node.js:130:18)\r\n    at /home/devops/goerli/lodestar/node_modules/@chainsafe/threads/dist/master/invocation-proxy.js:64:16\r\n    at new Subscription (/home/devops/goerli/lodestar/node_modules/observable-fns/dist/observable.js:159:40)\r\n    at Observable.subscribe (/home/devops/goerli/lodestar/node_modules/observable-fns/dist/observable.js:210:16)\r\n    at /home/devops/goerli/lodestar/node_modules/observable-fns/dist/multicast.js:31:49\r\n    at new Subscription (/home/devops/goerli/lodestar/node_modules/observable-fns/dist/observable.js:159:40)\r\n    at Observable.subscribe (/home/devops/goerli/lodestar/node_modules/observable-fns/dist/observable.js:210:16)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNo max listeners warnings\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nRun beacon node and validator client (with active validators), \r\n\r\n**Edit:** also observed this while running BN without attached validators\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Operating system\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Lodestar version or commit hash\r\n\r\nv1.9.0-rc.0",
